turn.2: Norðoyatunnilin  Norðoyatunnilin ("The Northern Isles Tunnel") is a two-lane road tunnel under the Leirvíksfjørður in the Faroe Islands.
turn.4: It connects the islands of Eysturoy and Borðoy.
turn.6: The tunnel is 6.3 km long and goes down to a depth of 150 metres below sea level.
turn.8: The maximum gradient is approximately 6 percent.
turn.10: The tunnel entrances are near the towns of Leirvík on Eysturoy, and Klaksvík on Borðoy.
turn.12: As of 2015, Norðoyatunnilin is the longest tunnel in the Faroe Islands.
